    <title>Combined summary - HTLC Endorsement for Jamming Mitigation</title>
    <updated>2023-07-08T02:40:53.122083+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2023-June/003984.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The email threads discuss the vulnerability of the Lightning Network's HTLC endorsement scheme and propose a reputation-based system to mitigate channel jamming attacks. The reputation system involves tracking reputation locally for each node's direct neighbors and allocating slots and liquidity based on their risk tolerance. The discussions also touch on the lack of transitivity in reputation acquisition cost, the impact of dynamic reputation windows on payment reliability, and the need for data gathering and experimentation to inform decision-making. There are also debates about the usefulness and implementation of reputation systems, as well as concerns about sudden behavioral changes and whitewashing attacks. The Lightning Network community is actively working on addressing these issues and improving routing and compensation systems.</summary>
